3
00:00:05,900 --> 00:00:07,240
Rob Lucci!

4
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:11,990
So they're really getting rid of Vegapunk?!

5
00:00:11,990 --> 00:00:15,500
Why are you here, pigeon jerk?!

6
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:20,540
This is a government island.

7
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:22,210
Oh, yeah!

8
00:00:22,210 --> 00:00:24,300
We're the ones out of place!

9
00:00:25,130 --> 00:00:27,720
Who cares about that now?!

10
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:30,300
Let's hurry to the upper level, Luffy!

11
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:32,640
What a pain in the neck!

12
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:34,560
The Straw Hats?!

13
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:36,930
And there's Jewelry Bonney.

14
00:00:37,310 --> 00:00:40,350
But don't attack them, Lucci!

15
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:44,820
Now that Straw Hat is an Emperor,
we need approval from the top to engage.

16
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,400
He's right.

17
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,950
The Four Emperors come with allies.

18
00:00:48,950 --> 00:00:51,570
A skirmish could lead to a war.

19
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:53,830
Report to the Marines at once.

20
00:00:53,830 --> 00:00:54,580
Yes, ma'am!

21
00:00:54,990 --> 00:00:57,830
I'm fully aware I shouldn't fight him...

22
00:01:01,870 --> 00:01:04,040
Take Bonney, Jinbe!

23
00:01:13,010 --> 00:01:14,390
What's going on?

24
00:01:15,140 --> 00:01:16,640
How awful!

25
00:01:18,390 --> 00:01:19,640
This girl...

26
00:01:20,310 --> 00:01:21,850
We just saw her!

27
00:01:22,310 --> 00:01:24,650
Chopper, check on her!

28
00:01:24,650 --> 00:01:25,570
Okay!

29
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:32,570
I'm afraid we'll need
Franky's expertise instead...

30
00:01:40,410 --> 00:01:42,420
Stay out of it.

31
00:01:42,420 --> 00:01:44,420
This is government business.

32
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:52,010
She gave us lots of food to eat!

33
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:33,650
The Straw Hats are on Egghead?!

34
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:35,110
Why?!

35
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:36,490
See?!

36
00:03:37,110 --> 00:03:40,410
Things are getting complicated again!

37
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:45,540
Does this mean Vegapunk
figured out CP0's mission?!

38
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:49,630
Yes. It's why they had to force their way in...

39
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:54,340
That's basically a declaration of war…

40
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:59,800
Those brats should've asked us first!

41
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:04,060
If Vegapunk has Straw Hat on his side,

42
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:07,020
we could suffer tremendous loss.

43
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,980
Where's Kizaru?

44
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:12,270
He's en route to Egghead...

45
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:16,030
for the mission we had
planned well in advance.

46
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:20,240
Tell Lucci to wait until the Marines arrive.

47
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,160
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

48
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:25,790
Do not permit him to fight Straw Hat!

49
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:32,960
Intruders! Evacuate immediately!

50
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,840
Evacuate immediately!

51
00:04:40,890 --> 00:04:42,930
Hey, pigeon!

52
00:04:42,930 --> 00:04:44,140
Where are you?!

53
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:47,230
Let's fight some more!

54
00:04:53,650 --> 00:04:56,730
You're just as flippant as ever.

55
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:00,070
It really pisses me off.

56
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,940
Straw Hat!

57
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:39,650
You're not the only one who's gotten stronger!

58
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,820
What's that?!

59
00:05:43,820 --> 00:05:46,490
Did Rob Lucci always look like that?!

60
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:51,460
Stop, Lucci! We don't have authorization!

61
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,800
What speed!

62
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,590
How rare that is!

63
00:05:59,590 --> 00:06:03,340
Most awakened zoan users
are robbed of their personality.

64
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:23,150
Kiss my ass!

65
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,880
Wait! Hold on, Luffy!

66
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,960
Think about your position!

67
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,630
This could cause a major uproar!

68
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:50,600
Shaka!

69
00:06:50,970 --> 00:06:53,310
Has the warrior in white appeared?

70
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:55,060
The real one!

71
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:57,020
But we just saw him down there!

72
00:06:59,150 --> 00:07:00,980
I can't believe it!

73
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:04,450
Tell me! What is this transformation...

74
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,660
he's undergone?!

75
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:09,030
We don't know much about it either!

76
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,580
Isn't it the Gum-Gum Fruit?

77
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:17,580
There is no such fruit...

78
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:22,300
in any of the old devil fruit encyclopedias!

79
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:23,260
What?!

80
00:07:23,970 --> 00:07:26,340
No, no! Even if you say that...

81
00:07:26,340 --> 00:07:29,050
He's always saying "Gum-Gum."

82
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:36,140
What a magnificent figure!

83
00:07:36,980 --> 00:07:39,900
This appearance of his...

84
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:42,900
resembles a being from old literature!

85
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:47,070
He is the spitting image of a god!

86
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:48,860
A god?!

87
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:50,320
This is Luffy!

88
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,700
You know, an idiot!

89
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:54,200
Indeed...

90
00:07:55,450 --> 00:08:00,500
The foolish and laughable Warrior of Liberation
who brings smiles to all people!

91
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:04,710
Also known as...

92
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:07,050
the Sun God,

93
00:08:07,050 --> 00:08:07,880
Nika!

94
00:08:11,260 --> 00:08:13,760
Nika? I've never heard that name before...

95
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,390
That's no surprise.

96
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:17,980
It was erased from history.

97
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:23,730
But he exists as long as people yearn for him!

98
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:28,150
All things are brought into
this world because of desires!

99
00:08:28,150 --> 00:08:29,990
For example...

100
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:32,450
the devil fruits!

101
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:33,450
What?!

102
00:08:33,450 --> 00:08:35,540
The devil fruits...

103
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:41,420
are manifestations of people's
aspirations for human evolution!

104
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,750
"I want to be like this."

105
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,710
"I want to be like that."

106
00:08:45,710 --> 00:08:49,680
The different powers represent
the diverse futures of humanity!

107
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:53,300
And so, that unnatural status
comes with a price:

108
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:57,480
to be loathed by the sea, the mother of nature!

109
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:01,900
Those with powers...

110
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:09,070
each live in different realities...

111
00:09:10,910 --> 00:09:13,200
born from someone's imagination!

112
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:21,170
That is my theory!

113
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:26,630
It's pointless to even ask whether a god exists!

114
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,800
Isn't this world so fascinating?!

115
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:39,560
These guys... Don't they
understand where they are?

116
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:43,690
This isn't a playground for
the government and pirates!

117
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:48,940
Today was meant to be my day off.

118
00:09:48,940 --> 00:09:50,780
What took you so long, Sentomaru?!

119
00:09:51,650 --> 00:09:53,910
Hey, Old Man Punk!

120
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:55,240
What should I do?

121
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,120
Cipher Pol is our ally!

122
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:59,200
Pirates are our enemies!

123
00:09:59,950 --> 00:10:02,920
Am I fighting alongside CP0?

124
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,840
No, not today, Sentomaru!

125
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:10,090
The thing is, CP0 is targeting me!

126
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:14,090
I'm afraid I must ask you to drive them away!

127
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:15,340
Wait a minute!

128
00:10:15,340 --> 00:10:16,970
That'll make me a traitor!

129
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,470
You're right.

130
00:10:19,470 --> 00:10:22,690
I need you to make a choice.

131
00:10:23,060 --> 00:10:24,600
Sentomaru...

132
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:27,570
Remember that you have to repay your debts.

133
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:29,570
The one who saved you...

134
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:31,240
from poverty...

135
00:10:31,610 --> 00:10:33,320
was me!

136
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,200
What'll it be?

137
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,200
Talk about pressure!

138
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:46,830
Is he about to strike?!

139
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:50,300
They possess three seraphim...

140
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,970
We're about to be in dire straits!

141
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,380
Hey, S-Bear!

142
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:56,590
Take one of them down!

143
00:10:58,050 --> 00:11:00,180
Don't move, S-Bear!

144
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:04,190
There's no chance, Kaku!
We have a worse hand!

145
00:11:04,190 --> 00:11:05,440
S-Bear!

146
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,400
Get rid of those agents!

147
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:13,530
Retreat!

148
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,750
We're in trouble...

149
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:26,540
Yeah...

150
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:31,500
Sentomaru overrides our authority chips!

151
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:32,630
Yeah.

152
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:39,510
The pacifista's orders are prioritized
based on who is issuing the orders.

153
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:43,680
First, the Five Elders are the highest priority.

154
00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:48,650
The second is Dr. Vegapunk.

155
00:11:49,690 --> 00:11:51,690
The third is Sentomaru.

156
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:56,990
Authority chip holders like us are the fourth.

157
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:01,660
No matter what we do,
Sentomaru has the final say!

158
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:06,290
Then we have to ask
the Five Elders to stop them!

159
00:12:06,290 --> 00:12:07,620
It's no use.

160
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:10,290
They must be commanded directly.

161
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:16,340
Even if it's the Five Elders, the pacifista
won't take orders through transponder snails!

162
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,800
And if you give it some thought,

163
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:24,310
taking out the seraphim means
a loss for the government!

164
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:25,270
Damn Lucci!

165
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,730
He should've looked before leaping!

166
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:47,620
Gum-Gum...

167
00:12:49,370 --> 00:12:50,210
Mole...

168
00:12:51,170 --> 00:12:53,130
Pistol!

169
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:00,470
Let's move!

170
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:01,970
S-Snake!

171
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:04,560
Get Straw Hat and the others
to the vacuum rocket!

172
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:07,220
They need to get to the Frontier Dome!

173
00:13:07,770 --> 00:13:09,730
S-Hawk! S-Shark!

174
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:11,730
Hold back the CP0 agents!

175
00:13:11,730 --> 00:13:15,190
Chopper, I can't believe my eyes!

176
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:20,320
Those darker-skinned people look like
the former Seven Warlords of the Sea!

177
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,450
Yeah!

178
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:23,660
It's quite the resemblance!

179
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:27,410
I can't believe they made clones out of us!

180
00:13:27,830 --> 00:13:30,750
Hey! Battle-axe!

181
00:13:33,290 --> 00:13:35,000
It's been a while!

182
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,380
Straw Hat!

183
00:13:38,010 --> 00:13:41,010
That's my weapon, not my name,
and don't act so happy to see me!

184
00:13:41,010 --> 00:13:43,220
We're enemies!

185
00:13:43,220 --> 00:13:46,930
Are you going to help
Old Man Punk get out of here?!

186
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:49,310
Yeah, he asked me to!

187
00:13:49,310 --> 00:13:50,140
No problem!

188
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:53,270
I don't know if I can count on you...

189
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:55,650
I can't believe you're an Emperor now!

190
00:13:55,650 --> 00:13:58,190
And that look of yours is ridiculous!

191
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,660
Hand Pistol!

192
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:14,630
Battle-axe!

193
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:17,500
The commander just needed to be eliminated...

194
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:21,720
Seraphim, follow our orders!

195
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:24,840
I'm sorry!

196
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,680
I distracted you!

197
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,180
Idiot...

198
00:14:30,930 --> 00:14:32,520
Don't underestimate me...

199
00:14:32,850 --> 00:14:34,520
I noticed it and...

200
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,400
Damn you!

201
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:50,620
I thought...

202
00:14:51,540 --> 00:14:52,750
I blocked it…

203
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:04,680
How persistent...

204
00:15:05,430 --> 00:15:08,050
Pass out already!

205
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:50,640
Your authority overrides ours,
so while you're conscious…

206
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:55,600
we can't control the seraphim!

207
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:21,750
Gum-Gum...

208
00:16:25,010 --> 00:16:26,760
Dawn...

209
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:31,390
Whip!

210
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:41,690
Lucci!

211
00:16:48,530 --> 00:16:50,070
Now is our chance!

212
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:51,740
Luffy, hurry up!

213
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:55,790
If you want to save this girl,
we must make haste to Vegapunk!

214
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:59,830
I'd love to, but...

215
00:16:59,830 --> 00:17:00,500
Huh?!

216
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:11,010
I can't stop!

217
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:19,480
Wh-What?!

218
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:21,020
Where are you going, Luffy?!

219
00:17:21,770 --> 00:17:25,900
I'm spinning too much!

220
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:29,190
Come back!

221
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:31,780
Take cover in the factory!

222
00:18:00,770 --> 00:18:03,020
The seraphim are unstoppable!

223
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:05,520
It's pointless to fight amongst ourselves!

224
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:07,020
And they're still children.

225
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:08,690
Their potential is terrifying.

226
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:11,490
Hey, Vegapunk!

227
00:18:13,610 --> 00:18:14,570
What's the matter?

228
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:18,290
That power is what's the matter!

229
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:20,660
See what tiny Jinbe is doing!

230
00:18:20,660 --> 00:18:23,670
Isn't that the Swim-Swim Fruit power?!

231
00:18:23,670 --> 00:18:25,170
The Swim-Swim Fruit?

232
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:26,540
That's right!

233
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:31,590
That's my sworn brother from
the Donquixote Family...

234
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:35,340
Senor Pink's power!

235
00:18:39,470 --> 00:18:42,890
There can't be two 
of the same fruit in this world!

236
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:45,730
Does this mean he died?!

237
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:50,400
Not my bro!

238
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,530
So you've noticed it.

239
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:55,910
This bro of yours is in Impel Down.

240
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:59,030
Then...

241
00:18:59,030 --> 00:19:01,700
You're saying you duplicated the devil fruit?!

242
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:05,170
That's right.

243
00:19:05,170 --> 00:19:07,380
The devil fruits...

244
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:13,470
can be made artificially
if they're the zoan type!

245
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:21,220
Well, Caesar's SMILE fruits are unacceptable...

246
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,810
Yeah, he can go to hell.

247
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:30,150
The SMILE fruits are too risky.

248
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:34,570
At best, one in ten people
will gain power by eating one.

249
00:19:34,570 --> 00:19:39,030
Everyone else without power
is forced to smile all the time...

250
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:39,870
How awful.

251
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,990
Caesar...

252
00:19:41,990 --> 00:19:44,960
Just hearing that name makes me wanna puke.

253
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:50,170
Well, putting that aside...

254
00:19:51,380 --> 00:19:55,800
I'm sure that every kind
of fruit can be replicated...

255
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:59,390
given tons of money and time!

256
00:20:01,260 --> 00:20:04,100
Though their awakening is yet to be seen.

257
00:20:11,610 --> 00:20:15,780
I did all I could to replicate
the logia types, to no avail...

258
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:16,990
But...

259
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,660
for the paramecia types,

260
00:20:20,660 --> 00:20:23,540
I found if I can get
the user's hereditary elements,

261
00:20:23,540 --> 00:20:27,290
I can create a special blood
infusion that, when administered,

262
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:29,920
allows someone else to have its power!

263
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,090
That's...

264
00:20:37,130 --> 00:20:40,140
the blood flowing through their arms!

265
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:43,600
The green blood!

266
00:20:45,970 --> 00:20:48,560
You made your own blood?!

267
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:52,980
Love-Love...

268
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,400
Mellow!

269
00:21:04,950 --> 00:21:10,250
The seraphim are the peak
of my scientific achievements!

270
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,750
Ursus Shock.

271
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:25,810
It can be said that they are...

272
00:21:26,930 --> 00:21:30,390
the strongest form of humanity ever known!

273
00:21:30,770 --> 00:21:33,100
Is that why the Seven
Warlords were abolished?!

274
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:37,860
You're insane for creating
something stronger than them!

275
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:41,070
They're essentially the Marines' weapons...

276
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:41,820
Yeah.

277
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:45,080
Their creation poses a threat to us.

278
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,590
Captain Sentomaru!

279
00:21:59,090 --> 00:21:59,800
Stay away!

280
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:03,800
He's still...

281
00:22:16,310 --> 00:22:18,610
Run, Captain Sentomaru!

282
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:23,570
Where did your silly friend go?

283
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,070
I don't know!

284
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:27,660
And he's not my friend!

285
00:22:28,030 --> 00:22:31,120
Shut your damn, traitorous mouth!

286
00:22:38,130 --> 00:22:39,050
Shave!

287
00:22:54,310 --> 00:22:56,940
Straw Hat!

288
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:48,820
You pest!

289
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:20,270
Gum-Gum...

290
00:24:22,860 --> 00:24:24,400
Dawn...

291
00:24:31,070 --> 00:24:34,540
Rocket!

292
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:39,870
Just how powerful did he get?!

293
00:24:42,630 --> 00:24:43,800
I'm close...

294
00:24:47,260 --> 00:24:49,090
to passing out!

295
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:02,900
This way! Hurry!

296
00:25:13,830 --> 00:25:14,580
Too slow!

297
00:25:17,330 --> 00:25:20,170
Why can't you speed things up?

298
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,790
That's the vacuum rocket!

299
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:25,170
Get on it now!

300
00:25:26,130 --> 00:25:27,800
Oh, thanks!

301
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:30,180
You're a kind Hancock!

302
00:25:31,180 --> 00:25:32,300
Thanks!

303
00:25:32,300 --> 00:25:33,930
You've been a big help!

304
00:25:33,930 --> 00:25:35,260
I-Insolence!

305
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:38,520
I'm just following orders!

306
00:25:43,350 --> 00:25:46,320
The rocket will depart in one minute.

307
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:48,860
Hey! Luffy!

308
00:25:48,860 --> 00:25:50,950
Hurry up!

309
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:55,990
Oh no!

310
00:25:55,990 --> 00:25:59,200
Please refrain from rushing onto the rocket.

311
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,370
Straw Hat!

312
00:26:04,130 --> 00:26:07,750
I trust you with Old Man Punk!

313
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:10,760
Alright!

314
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,180
Leave it to me!

315
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,720
Stop! Go the other way!

316
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:21,600
The doors are closing.

317
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:22,940
Please be careful.

318
00:26:33,820 --> 00:26:35,660
We'll get him off the island...

319
00:26:37,870 --> 00:26:40,450
at any cost!

320
00:26:59,140 --> 00:27:00,350
Now departing.

321
00:27:06,690 --> 00:27:07,900
I've never been on such–

322
00:27:15,490 --> 00:27:18,370
This is quite something!

323
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:21,540
Where am I?! Where's Vegapunk?!

324
00:27:24,330 --> 00:27:27,210
I can still fight…

325
00:27:27,210 --> 00:27:29,090
What?! Who are you?!

326
00:27:29,090 --> 00:27:30,710
That's Luffy!
A lot has happened!

327
00:27:30,710 --> 00:27:32,460
I'll tell you later!

328
00:27:32,460 --> 00:27:33,840
This is ridiculous!

329
00:27:35,930 --> 00:27:38,470
Oh, I think I'm getting
used to– Nope! Too fast!

330
00:27:38,470 --> 00:27:39,760
Shut up, ship doc!

331
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:40,510
So fast...

332
00:27:40,510 --> 00:27:43,980
How long are you gonna
be like that, Straw Hat?!

333
00:27:48,150 --> 00:27:51,520
Departing the Fabriophase,
bound for the Labophase.

334
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,320
Transit duration:

335
00:27:58,490 --> 00:27:59,870
thirty-two seconds.

336
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:02,580
Arrived.

337
00:28:02,580 --> 00:28:03,870
How fast!

338
00:28:03,870 --> 00:28:06,920
All subsequent rockets are canceled.

339
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:09,210
The Labophase, Egghead.

340
00:28:09,210 --> 00:28:11,170
Frontier Dome now fortified.

341
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:13,300
Intruder alert.

342
00:28:13,300 --> 00:28:14,630
Danger.

343
00:28:14,630 --> 00:28:20,090
Researchers, please evacuate
to the factory and seal the building.

344
00:28:27,270 --> 00:28:28,980
You're admirable in a way...

345
00:28:30,940 --> 00:28:34,110
You did fulfill your duty for Vegapunk...

346
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:36,740
as his bodyguard.

347
00:28:37,490 --> 00:28:38,450
So...

348
00:28:38,950 --> 00:28:41,120
it's a shame, Sentomaru.

349
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:45,450
The Marines told us to wait for their arrival.

350
00:28:45,450 --> 00:28:47,540
How could they take this so lightly?

351
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,080
If we wait, he'll run!

352
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:53,340
Are they really trying to kill you?!

353
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:56,010
You're the smartest man in the world, right?!

354
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:59,510
It would be the government's loss if you died!

355
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:00,720
Yes, I suppose.

356
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:04,600
But try placing yourself in
the shoes of the higher-ups.

357
00:29:05,930 --> 00:29:10,730
My inventions have been
beneficial to the government.

358
00:29:10,730 --> 00:29:14,480
Innovations using seastone in navigation technology.

359
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:16,860
The production of cyborg animals.

360
00:29:17,490 --> 00:29:21,950
I've also studied the devil fruits
and successfully applied my findings.

361
00:29:21,950 --> 00:29:24,870
I made human weapons, the pacifista.

362
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:27,250
And...

363
00:29:27,910 --> 00:29:30,290
I completed the seraphim!

364
00:29:30,670 --> 00:29:36,250
So if I moved against you as
the world's greatest intelligence, what then?!

365
00:29:36,590 --> 00:29:37,800
You're right...

366
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:39,510
I'd be pissed!

367
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:42,010
I'd off you!

368
00:29:42,010 --> 00:29:43,220
Don't "off" him!

369
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:48,560
I don't even have the slightest
intention of revolting,

370
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:52,400
but those hard-headed people
firmly believe that I do.

371
00:29:52,770 --> 00:29:56,270
Well, that's just the way the cookie crumbles.

372
00:29:56,270 --> 00:29:58,990
Don't say it like it's someone else's problem!

373
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:03,570
Then your group led by one of
the Four Emperors showed up.

374
00:30:03,570 --> 00:30:05,910
It must be fate, then!

375
00:30:05,910 --> 00:30:06,450
Huh?

376
00:30:07,580 --> 00:30:09,450
You'll come aboard our ship?!

377
00:30:09,950 --> 00:30:11,460
You're most welcome!

378
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:14,290
Super!

379
00:30:14,290 --> 00:30:17,090
Check out the General Franky!

380
00:30:17,090 --> 00:30:20,550
And the Sunny... Check her out too!

381
00:30:20,550 --> 00:30:23,380
Really?! He's coming aboard?!

382
00:30:23,380 --> 00:30:24,760
That's a huge burden!

383
00:30:25,140 --> 00:30:26,930
Don't worry, Nami!

384
00:30:26,930 --> 00:30:28,260
I've got you!

385
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,600
I'm counting on you!

386
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:32,520
Do your best-quasar!

387
00:30:32,940 --> 00:30:33,640
Hey!

388
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,770
Why don't you free our feet, then?!

389
00:30:36,150 --> 00:30:37,480
You jerk!

390
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:40,150
Dr. Atlas!

391
00:30:40,150 --> 00:30:41,110
Oh no!

392
00:30:41,110 --> 00:30:42,570
This is serious!

393
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:44,700
We'll take care of you right away!

394
00:30:45,030 --> 00:30:48,490
Prepare to treat and repair her ASAP!

395
00:30:48,490 --> 00:30:50,790
Thank you for bringing her in!

396
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,160
Leave her to us!

397
00:30:52,500 --> 00:30:53,870
Yeah, thanks.

398
00:30:53,870 --> 00:30:56,630
You guys! Where's Vegapunk?

399
00:30:57,790 --> 00:30:59,130
I know he's here!

400
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:01,380
Tell me!

401
00:31:01,380 --> 00:31:03,300
Hey! Stop it!

402
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:04,760
Calm down a little!

403
00:31:09,180 --> 00:31:10,930
So this is his lab!

404
00:31:12,430 --> 00:31:14,060
Cool!

405
00:31:14,060 --> 00:31:15,560
Look at this place!

406
00:31:17,190 --> 00:31:18,900
That bastard!

407
00:31:19,230 --> 00:31:21,110
I will make him pay!

408
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:27,740
Bonney, where are you going?!

409
00:31:31,790 --> 00:31:35,790
If Vegapunk's response to my request
to change my father back...

410
00:31:37,460 --> 00:31:39,040
is those bugs...

411
00:31:43,170 --> 00:31:45,170
I have no choice but to kill him!

412
00:31:45,170 --> 00:31:47,800
Y-You're just taking it out on him...

413
00:31:49,050 --> 00:31:50,640
Wait!

414
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:52,180
Stop, Bonney!

415
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:54,390
Hey! Bonney!

416
00:32:07,910 --> 00:32:10,780
Our authority chips are back in effect.

417
00:32:10,780 --> 00:32:13,290
The seraphim are now ours.

418
00:32:13,830 --> 00:32:15,620
The tide has turned!

419
00:32:16,330 --> 00:32:18,620
I took down one of the satellites.

420
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:24,210
Including Vegapunk's
main body, there are six left.

421
00:32:24,210 --> 00:32:27,220
Sounds about right.

422
00:32:27,220 --> 00:32:28,050
But...

423
00:32:28,550 --> 00:32:31,260
that defense system is formidable.

424
00:32:33,510 --> 00:32:36,520
I won't let even an ant off this island!

425
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:38,270
Destroy every ship here!

426
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:40,230
Block off all escape routes, too!

427
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:43,860
Don't let them get away!

428
00:32:55,370 --> 00:32:59,250
So the Straw Hats are siding with Vegapunk.

429
00:33:00,170 --> 00:33:03,130
That gives him a means of escape.

430
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:08,590
But it probably...

431
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:15,470
won't turn out the way he imagines.

432
00:33:17,850 --> 00:33:20,770
Proceed as planned.

433
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:23,480
Send all available ships…

434
00:33:25,190 --> 00:33:27,280
to Egghead.

